      <abstract id="Abs1">
        <p>We report the case of a
woman with an apparent primary
thunderclap headache which
occurred frequently until she
achieved a therapeutic dosage of
gabapentin. Primary thunderclap
headache is a rare type of headache
that warrants significant testing to
rule out more ominous possibilities.
Whether gabapentin may help other
primary thunderclap headache sufferers
or not remains unclear.
Further research is needed.</p>
      </abstract>
